1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Hello, child! I'm Grandma Sankofa. Come with me, way back in time.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:28,000
More, more, even more, before the cell phone, before the TV, before the book, before the writing, before the school, 3,200,000 years ago.

3
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Here she is, Lucinha. She is 4 years old. She lives in Ethiopia, in the east of the African continent, and she has a special thing.

4
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Look, look well, Lucinha is standing, on her two feet, walking. Lucinha is one of the first girls we know who walked upright in our great and ancient family.

5
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Before her, many millions of years ago, other children also walked upright, in Chad, in Kenya, in Ethiopia.

6
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:19,000
But Lucinha is the most famous of all. A little girl, 3 million years ago, walking in the African savannah.

7
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Shall we sing to me, Lucinha?

8
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Do you know how we know about Lucinha? Scientists, people who study the past, found her bones, in 1974, in Ethiopia.

9
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:32,000
And do you know the name they gave her? Lucy, because of a Beatles song that played in the camp.

10
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Do you know something? Every time you walk on foot, every time you run, jump, dance, you are doing what Lucinha started, 3 million years ago.

11
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:54,000
She is part of our very ancient family, from all over the world.

12
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Do you remember my name? Sankofa. It is an ancient word from the people of Akan, in Ghana.

13
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:09,000
It means, come back, go, look, come back in time, look for history.

14
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Learn with those who came before, you are part of this story, child.

15
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Bye. Walking on foot is a very ancient thing. I am the bones. Sankofa.

16
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,000
See you next time.

